8.20	Chateau_Petrus	Pétrus (wine)	Pétrus is a Bordeaux wine estate located in the Pomerol appellation near its eastern border to Saint-Émilion. An estate of limited size, it produces a limited production red wine almost entirely from Merlot grapes, on occasion with small amounts of Cabernet Franc, and produces no second wine. The estate belongs to the family of the Libourne wine merchant JP Moueix.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1f/Petrus03.jpg/220px-Petrus03.jpg
